\begin_layout Standard

\series bold
Inclusion Criteria
\series default
:
 A term warrants a Glossary entry if it meets any of the following conditions:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
The term is coined by the ECIO Policy Manual and has no standard external definition (e.g.,
 "Hard Fork," "Operational Handback").
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
The term is a standard industry or framework term that the manual uses with a specific institutional meaning that narrows,
 modifies,
 or contextualizes the common definition (e.g.,
 "Incident Commander" as scoped by the ECIO framework).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
The term is an acronym or abbreviation whose expansion is not obvious to the intended audience of the manual.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\series bold
Exclusion Criteria
\series default
:
 The following shall not receive Glossary entries:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Plain-language terms used in their ordinary,
 commonly understood sense (e.g.,
 "server," "firewall," "email").
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Terms whose meaning is fully self-evident to a competent IT professional without further definition.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
External framework terms (e.g.,
 NIST control names,
 COBIT process identifiers) that are used in their standard published meaning without institutional modification.
 These terms are defined by their issuing authority and do not require local redefinition.
\end_layout

